 from the time I was born, I had stars in my eyes so he called me Staria. Now he says that it was too true of a name since I always have my head in the clouds. My mother cried the day the messenger came with a note that the order of the monks needed another to help them. <br>
My father was too old and crippled to return to the order he so loved. Being the only child and not the son that was hoped for, they balked at sending me in his stead. I insisted on going. I may not be male but I'm just as strong and twice as cunning. I vow to do my family name proud and left while the moon was being chased out of the sky by the sun.<br>
<br>
Day One-<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Finally, I've found the city of Qeynos. Not exactly full of beauty but I do see alot of my own here. Carrying a tattered note in my hand, I seek out the clanhouse. Everyone once in awhile I hear the shouts of Fippy Darkpaw raging against the slaying of his people and the beggings of another man to come to the Temple of Light and not fight. Odd but I continue on. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Following the directions on the note, I find the clan leader and give it to him. He welcomes me into the order and gives me a tunic. Upon putting it on, I find it's not much of shirt..more of a bare covering of my female assets. I get some training and head out on my first quest to prove myself. Slaying bats and rats moves me quickly towards my second level. My quest to bring back 4 gnoll pup scalps is trying to me. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp A halfling druid asks for my assistance in buying him some sap from a girl behind the bar in Crows tavern. Apparently she doesn't have a likeness for him. He repays my service with 10 platinum. Not bad for 20 minutes of my time along with the spells of strength and speed he casts on my before i return to land outside the city to fight. He also suggests I go to a place called black burrow in the hills of Qeynos to get my scalps. Not sure if my skills are high enough to travel yet but I'm willing to try tomorrow.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I've learned quite a few things in my first day. My kick and punch is getting stronger. I've also found the my looks can get me help when i need it from the males of all races. Not exactly the way I like to do things, but I suppose if it will save my life or further my studies, I will use it to my advantage. Perhaps tomorrow I will find someone to talk to about such things but for now, I'll sleep.<br>
<br>
Staria<br>
Human Monk of the 2nd Season<br>
